http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Thieves-target-car-showroom-in-K.R.-Pet/article14016921.ece

Some unidentified persons have stolen a multi-utility vehicle, cash and other material from a locked Maruti car showroom at K.R. Pet in Mandya district on Friday night.Police sources said the culprits had gained entry into the Mandovi Motors showroom by cutting the iron rods of a window and taken away a brand new vehicle that had been kept for display inside the showroom, Rs. 25,000 in cash that was lying in the counter, keys of some other cars that were on display, television sets and other material from there.The crime might have taken place between Friday midnight and early hours of Saturday.Security arrangementsThe burglary came to light at around 9 a.m. on Saturday when the workers arrived for their duty, according to the K.R. Pet police.There were no surveillance cameras installed in the showroom.There were no security guards to keep vigil at night. Even sirens or burglar alarms were not installed in the showroom, a senior police official said.SuspicionAccording to the police, persons having thorough knowledge about lack of safety measures in the showroom must have been involved in the burglary.Dog squadDeputy Superintendent of Police H.N. Janardhan (Nagamangala subdivision) and finger print experts inspected the crime scene. Sniffer dog squad was also pressed into service.A case has been registered in this regard.